{"id":"alleluia","term":"Alleluia","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>The Greek form (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 19:1\">Rev. 19:1</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 19:3\">3</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 19:4\">4</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 19:6\">6</a>) of the Hebrew Hallelujah = Praise ye Jehovah, which begins or ends several of the psalms (106, 111, 112, 113, etc.).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Revelation 19:1","Revelation 19:3","Revelation 19:4","Revelation 19:6"]}